ates the very exclusions it critiques but also creates a disempowering haze of indecision. She shows that reasoning through paradox has become deeply problematic: it engrains a startling homogeneity of thought while undercutting the commitment to social justice that remains a guiding imperative of theory. Rather than calling for a wholesale abandonment of such reasoning, Anker argues for an expanded, diversified theory toolkit that can help theorists escape the seductions and traps of paradox.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCritical theory. 0aParadoxxPolitical aspects. 0aParadoxxSocial aspects. 0aParadox. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076691208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2022 Englishz978311099276208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2022z9783110992755oZDB-23-DPH40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478023609?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478023609423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478023609/original  a978-3-11-076691-2  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099276-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-DPHb2022